{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17487342","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17487342"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T03:06:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T03:06:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"325"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"325","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/325"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.41,0.14,0.08,0.33]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"325"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"98662"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"325","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/325"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"325"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"81056"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"333"},{"type":"tags","id":"498"},{"type":"tags","id":"853"},{"type":"tags","id":"934"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1052"},{"type":"tags","id":"4578"},{"type":"tags","id":"5772"},{"type":"tags","id":"9076"},{"type":"tags","id":"9097"},{"type":"tags","id":"9103"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"17621"},{"type":"contributions","id":"33820"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38840"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"98662","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/98662"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 81-year-old man is admitted with a two day history of crampy abdominal pain, distension, nausea and vomiting. His medical history includes hypertension, type 2 diabetes and an appendicectomy at the age of 45. He takes perindopril and metformin. On examination his abdomen is distended, but soft to palpation. He has numerous high-pitched bowel sounds. A plain abdominal X-ray is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Caecal volvulus","Gallstone ileus","Large bowel obstruction","Carcinoma of the caecum","Adhesive-obstruction"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe X-ray shows a large volume of gas in the small bowel - consistent with obstruction (Image 1). In addition, there is a calcified and laminated structure within one of the bowel loops in the pelvis. Most tellingly, gas can be seen in the biliary tree (Image 2). All the three X-rays are from the same patient. All this adds up to a diagnosis of \u003Cstrong\u003Egallstone ileus\u003C/strong\u003E. At some stage in the past the patient has had one or more episodes of cholecystitis. These episodes may not have been of sufficient severity for the patient to seek medical help. As a result of the resulting inflammatory process there has been fistula formation between the gallbladder and an adjacent piece of small bowel - most likely the duodenum. This has widened over time to allow the stone to pass into the intestine and air from the gut to enter the biliary tree. In this case the stone is of such a size that it has lead to obstruction.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gallstone ileus is a very uncommon cause of small bowel obstruction."],"references":["Chang L, Chang M, Chang HM, Chang AI, Chang F. Clinical and radiological diagnosis of gallstone ileus: a mini review.\u00a0Emerg Radiol. 2018;25(2):189-196. doi:10.1007/s10140-017-1568-5","Ayantunde AA, Agrawal A. Gallstone ileus: diagnosis and management.\u00a0World J Surg. 2007;31(6):1292-1297. doi:10.1007/s00268-007-9011-9"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"81056"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"325"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"14414"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20409"},{"type":"media","id":"20410"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"14414","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/14414"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/e5f124a0-04b1-40fd-a237-593da65d91e0.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/e5f124a0-04b1-40fd-a237-593da65d91e0.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":358,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"20409","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20409"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/1l1wWX0ZvcmbZs0A5thIjlS8KU9jcR.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/1l1wWX0ZvcmbZs0A5thIjlS8KU9jcR.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":514,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"20410","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20410"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/p1jvvoiHa5l7sJuIlnsOGUVBCUNbdI.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/p1jvvoiHa5l7sJuIlnsOGUVBCUNbdI.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":514,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"81056","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/81056"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-16T09:07:29+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-16T09:08:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"325"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"98662"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"5","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2d","name":"Gastroenterology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGro